        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4821&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=to+Tauruse%2E%2E%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Tauruse,</P><P>I understand where you’re coming from. Though I haven’t played EQ for 3 years (yet) I do have a very firm understanding of what has happened over time in terms of balancing.</P><P>I don’t think EQ was initially designed to handle what it is currently doing. This is a VERY important point! It's like trying to stuff 5pounds of crap into a 3pound bag. Verant never even dreamed EQ would become THE most popular game w/ 420,000 accounts. In fact even the dev's themselves have indirectly stated that it would be easier to start over than to try to fix the current EQ. And that is exactly what is happening.... EQ2 is being developed and released soon. </P><P>So the only thing I can say is just to let it go and jump ship to another game when the opportunity arises. I know I wont be going to EQ2 simply due to the way that verant has handled EQ1. The nerfs, the bad CS, stealth changes, their inability to have foresight, etc. </P><P>EQ1 was an experiment, it was mostly successful. Now that the MMONG beta phase is over.... a new crop of well designed, well managed games are coming out. Verant knows that EQ1 has limited life left, they see all the other games coming and know that if they don’t adapt they will be pushed out of business or have their profit severely reduced. But I like to think they slit their own throats by mis-managing EQ1. Many users of EQ1 have bitter memories of verant, and since EQ2 will be a fresh new start many of those users will choose to start fresh somewhere else besides the EQ world.</P><P>And like you Tauruse, I am upset at the way verant has handled EQ1. They ask us to invest hundreds of hours into something and then act surprised when we (users) take things to heart. How could we NOT get emotional when our 2 year old 50+ character has a change applied to them? And this isn’t only about our valuable time (some of us have family's and jobs, and aren't carefree teenagers), it's also about the $$ we spent to get EQ to run! They force us to get new hardware and software (SOL forced out Win95 users, and also to have us upgrade our hardware so luclin would run reasonably well). So after I spend all this time and all this $$, they change something and then act surprised when a wave of users start ranting on their boards (which they eventually closed). </P><P>So many of us are like you tauruse, jaded.</P><P><BR>Meridak Souldefiler<BR>58th Defiler of karana</P><P></font></td>

